\fs24 \cf0 	Grunt looked out from his perch up on the trees.  He hated this job.  Nothing exiting ever happened to a lookout twenty feet in the air.  Especially when someone would have to travel through hundreds of troops just to reach his tree.  One would have to be mad...\
	Just after Grunt thought this he saw a figure moving his way.  He was dressed in tan pants and a white shirt, with a green robe and a 1\'bd foot long pointy green hat.  In one hand he held a sword and in the other a shield - the shield of an enemy.  Exited, Grunt raised a horn to his lips and blew.  Immediately, thousands of troops ran at the figure, and multiple archers raised their bows.  But the figure had weapons like none of them had seen.\
	He had black rocks that exploded.  They alone killed easily half the troops.  Then there was his mask; it gave him the eyesight of a hawk, easily allowing him to shoot the archers with his bow.  The bow itself was wonderful, light yet sturdy, able to shoot things hundreds of yards away.\
	By now, Grunt was starting to get worried.  As the last of the reinforcements arrived, he realized if someone didn't do something fast, they would all die.  He stood up, raised his bow, and fired.  The arrow hit the man in the neck, and he sank.  He looked at Grunt with his piercing blue eyes, then died, crumpling in a heap.\
	Meanwhile, in a nearby village, a baby was born...\
